injury.description: Isaac won't play Monday against the Pelicans due to a right hamstring strain, Khobi Price of the Orlando Sentinel reports.

The Timberwolves are hopeful that Towns (calf) will be ready to return to the court at some point during their final "10-to-15 games" of the season, Shams Charania reported Tuesday during his "FanDuel TV" segment.
Head coach Chris Finch said Prince isn't traveling with the Timberwolves on their current four-game road trip, which began Sunday at Golden State, Chris Hine of the Minneapolis Star Tribune reports.
Yurtseven (ankle) has been ruled out for Monday's matchup against Philadelphia.
Jovic (back) has been ruled out for Monday's matchup against Philadelphia.
Lowry (knee) has been downgraded to out Monday against the 76ers.

Brown (personal) remains out for Monday's matchup against the Knicks, but head coach Joe Mazzulla said he expects the shooting guard to be back in the starting lineup Wednesday versus the Cavaliers, Souichi Terada of The Springfield Republican reports.
Gallinari (knee) said Sunday in an interview with Gianluca Bortolomai of AroundTheGame.com that his goal remains to return to game action at some point during the Celtics' postseason run.
Gillespie (lower leg)  remains out Tuesday against Houston and is without a clear timetable.
Nnaji (shoulder)   remains out Tuesday against Houston.
Stewart (hip) has been ruled out for Monday's game against Charlotte.
Ivey is listed as out for Monday's game against the Hornets due to personal reasons.

The Raptors announced Tuesday that Porter underwent season-ending surgery on his left foot, Marc J. Spears of ESPN.com reports.
Porzingis (knee) is doubtful for Tuesday's game against Atlanta.
Morris (back) is questionable for Tuesday's game against Atlanta.
Shamet (foot) has been ruled out for Friday's game versus the Thunder and will be re-evaluated in a week, Gerald Bourguet of GoPHNX.com reports.

Washington (foot) has been ruled out for Monday's game against Detroit.
Dedmon (hip) is expected to be out for "a few more games," Austin Krell of USA Today reports.
Liddell (knee) signed a two-way contract with the Pelicans on Sunday.

Kleber (hamstring) is questionable for Tuesday's game against Indiana.

Porter (foot) is questionable for Tuesday's matchup against the Nuggets.

Clarkson has been ruled out for Tuesday's game against the Spurs due to a right thumb sprain.

Holmgren (foot) underwent a successful secondary procedure Tuesday to remove hardware from his initial Lisfranc surgery in August, Michael Scotto of USA Today reports.
Pokusevski (lower leg) was spotted on the court Monday doing some light shooting, Andrew Schlecht of The Athletic reports.
Winslow (ankle) has yet to resume full-contact activity and remains out indefinitely, Sean Highkin of RoseGardenReport.com reports.
Simons (ankle) is progressing in his recovery but remains without a timetable for a return, Sean Highkin of RoseGardenReport.com reports.
Badji (knee) remains without a timetable for a return.

Iguodala (hip) has been ruled out for Tuesday's matchup against Portland.

Green (knee) is probable for Tuesday's matchup against Portland.

Russell (ankle) is doubtful for Tuesday's matchup against the Grizzlies, Jovan Buha of The Athletic reports.
